==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rollic
<hw>Rol"lic</hw> <pr>(r⟦ocr⟧l"l⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rollicked</conjf>
<pr>(-l⟦icr⟧kt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Rollicking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Corrupt. fr.
<ets>frolic</ets>, under the influence of <ets>roll</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To move or play in a careless, swaggering manner, with a frolicsome
air; to frolic; to sport; commonly in the form
<xex>rollicking</xex>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He described his friends as <qex>rollicking</qex> blades.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Hook.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rollichie</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Rollejee</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Rolliche</ent>⟦br⟧
